        <prj:TechnicalJustification>
            <prj:justificationText>The selected Band 4 transitions N$_2$D$^+$(2-1) and DNC(2-1) trace very high density cold gas, with effective densities of 10$^5$ and 4$\times$10$^5$, respectively. These are the lowest-J transitions (expected to be strongest) of these molecules available in ALMA Cycle 2.  We expect line strengths of order 100-200 mJy/beam (Tan et al. 2013). Being conservative, we require a sensitivity of 5mJy/beam. To make sure the lines are well resolved, we request the highest spectral resolution (0.06km/s) to ensure several channels cover the expected 0.5km/s linewidiths. This limits us to the two lines because of the high data rate restriction. At this resolution, we require 31 minutes of 12m array time to cover the three pointings. To circumvent unequal spatial filtering scales between the N$_2$H$^+$ data and proposed maps, we request ACA observations of these lines as well. This adds 2 hours of observation. The total requested time is 2.58h accroding to the OT estimator assuming the default values of pwv.  We are confident that the conditions are appropriate to excite the proposed transitions (see Fig.3), and that these data will provide accurate kinematic and chemical information to achieve our goals. </prj:justificationText>
        </prj:TechnicalJustification>
